$$\mathbf{u} = \frac{\mathbf{v}}{\|\mathbf{v}\|} = \frac{1}{\sqrt{1^2 + 7^2}} \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 7 \end{pmatrix} = \frac{1}{\sqrt{50}} \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 7 \end{pmatrix}$$

Now, the projection matrix $\mathbf{P}$ is simply the outer product of this unit vector with itself:

$$\mathbf{P} = \mathbf{u} \mathbf{u}^T = \frac{1}{\sqrt{50}} \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 7 \end{pmatrix} \left( \frac{1}{\sqrt{50}} \begin{pmatrix} 1 & 7 \end{pmatrix} \right) = \begin{pmatrix} \frac{1}{50} & \frac{7}{50} \\ \frac{7}{50} & \frac{49}{50} \end{pmatrix}$$



\begin{equation*}
\boxed{\mathbf{P} = \begin{pmatrix} \frac{1}{50} & \frac{7}{50} \\ \frac{7}{50} & \frac{49}{50} \end{pmatrix}}
\end{equation*} 



